=head1 DESCRIPTION

Describes public access policies that apply to the Amazon S3 bucket.

For information about each of the following settings, see Blocking
public access to your Amazon S3 storage
(https://docs.aws.amazon.com/AmazonS3/latest/userguide/access-control-block-public-access.html)
in the I<Amazon S3 User Guide>.

=head1 ATTRIBUTES


=head2 PublicAclAccess => Str

Indicates whether or not there is a setting that allows public access
to the Amazon S3 buckets through access control lists (ACLs).


=head2 PublicAclIgnoreBehavior => Str

Indicates whether or not there is a setting that ignores all public
access control lists (ACLs) on the Amazon S3 bucket and the objects
that it contains.


=head2 PublicBucketRestrictBehavior => Str

Indicates whether or not there is a setting that restricts access to
the bucket with specified policies.


=head2 PublicPolicyAccess => Str

Indicates whether or not there is a setting that allows public access
to the Amazon S3 bucket policy.



